# API design

- Clean, predictable REST under `/api/*`
- Consistent `{ success, data?, error? }` JSON
- Document new endpoints in `API_ENDPOINTS.md`
- No duplicate or unnecessary routes

# Error handling

- Use centralized middleware in `server.js` — avoid copy-pasted try/catch in every controller
- Throw or `next(err)` with `status` for predictable client errors
- Same error shape everywhere: `{ success: false, error: "..." }`

# Performance

- Fetch only required fields (`select`, lean queries when appropriate)
- Avoid N+1 queries; batch or populate intentionally
- No redundant DB round-trips per request

# Security

- Never log or return passwords/tokens in responses
- Validate inputs (`express-validator` in routes)
- Secrets in `.env` only — never commit credentials

# Dependencies

- Do not add npm packages unless necessary
- Prefer built-in Node, Express, Mongoose, and existing deps in `package.json`

# Consistency & scalability

- Follow existing file layout and naming (`*Controller.js`, `routes/*.js`)
- New features should extend services without rewriting core modules
- Shared logic → `services/` or `utils/`, not duplicated in controllers
